<br>
Incorrect.  Rotations were started so the &quot;big&quot; guilds could share mobs.  As other guilds kill we let them onto the rotation.  They are not here to protect smaller guilds, however it is a nice side benefit.<br>
<br>
Rotations and the RTA in general are compromises.  Sometimes the big guild give up something, some times the little guild give up something.  BotS agrees to only kill Trak once in 3 months, even though they can kill him with an exp group... Clan Bashemded agrees to leave not kill Ikky and Eashan. <p><P><A HREF="http://www.jakefitch.com/asb/char_detail.asp?Name=Milambus" TARGET="_blank"><IMG SRC="http://jakefitch.com/sig/eq/sig1.jpg" HEIGHT="150" WIDTH="400" ALT="Milambus Mandragon" BORDER="0"></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uemilsinclair.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Emil Sinclair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 319<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/16/02 10:32:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=123.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ToVN Rotation agreement/rules</span><hr size=1> you are looking at it from your perspective:<br>
